 The logarithmic function $f(x) = \log{x}$ is neither an even nor an odd function. This is because an even function has the property $f(x) = f(-x)$ for all $x$ in its domain, while an odd function has the property $f(-x) = -f(x)$ for all $x$ in its domain. However, for $f(x) = \log{x}$, this is not the case. 

\begin{align*}
\log{(-x)} \neq \log{x} \quad \text{and} \quad \log{(-x)} \neq -\log{x}
\end{align*}

</think> The answer is neither.

